WEBVTT

00:28.194 --> 00:31.698
(engine humming)

00:39.572 --> 00:42.409
(laboured breathing)

01:00.660 --> 01:02.495
(laboured breathing)

01:58.985 --> 02:04.090
(deep breath)

02:04.090 --> 02:06.526
(birds singing)

02:46.499 --> 02:47.600
(piano note)

02:54.274 --> 02:56.442
♪

03:35.415 --> 03:36.883
(sighing)

03:50.530 --> 03:52.599
(sighing)

04:04.210 --> 04:05.478
(sniffling)

04:12.185 --> 04:13.953
- (cab driver): Thanks a lot.
- Thanks.

04:51.057 --> 04:52.825
(deep breath)

04:54.427 --> 04:57.530
(running footsteps)
(child laughing)

05:24.657 --> 05:27.527
(audible breathing)

05:39.605 --> 05:41.774
- (child): Dad!
- (man): What?

05:41.774 --> 05:43.810
You ready?

05:43.810 --> 05:46.112
Yeah? Let's go.

06:00.526 --> 06:02.528
(children laughing)

06:11.404 --> 06:14.474
Give me a big hug. Be good.

06:37.930 --> 06:39.465
- Hi, Dan.

06:41.200 --> 06:43.403
I just wanted
to say that...

06:43.403 --> 06:46.239
I'm OK, and I'm back now.

06:48.174 --> 06:50.276
- When did you get back?

06:50.276 --> 06:52.678
- Today.
Now. Just now.

06:56.516 --> 06:59.218
- And you thought
that you could just show up

06:59.218 --> 07:01.854
whenever you wanted,
and we'd just be

07:01.854 --> 07:03.890
waiting here
with a cake and banner or...

07:03.890 --> 07:05.858
- Dan...

07:05.858 --> 07:07.593
- Well, you didn't think
to tell us anything,

07:07.593 --> 07:10.430
give us an idea
when you'd be back?

07:10.430 --> 07:12.865
- I'm here.
I'm back.

07:12.865 --> 07:14.500
- OK, but it's not...
that's not how it works.

07:18.104 --> 07:21.040
- Dan, when can I see Isabel?
- What are you talking about?

07:23.309 --> 07:26.145
What? So you're OK now?

07:26.145 --> 07:28.147
- Yeah, I am.

07:28.147 --> 07:30.883
- Yeah? What's your plan?
Where are you staying?

07:30.883 --> 07:32.118
- I'm staying
at my dad's for a little while--

07:32.118 --> 07:34.487
- Good for you.

07:34.487 --> 07:36.622
Hmm...

07:41.561 --> 07:43.329
- Dan, I want to see her.

07:43.329 --> 07:45.565
- She doesn't remember you.

07:56.742 --> 07:58.678
Can I call you now?
Am I allowed?

08:01.314 --> 08:03.015
- Of course.

08:05.151 --> 08:06.419
- I need to think.

08:10.623 --> 08:12.425
♪

08:23.703 --> 08:26.005
- (woman):    Isabel,

08:26.005 --> 08:28.307
one night

08:28.307 --> 08:30.476
I went in to check on you,

08:30.476 --> 08:33.779
and you were lying there awake.

08:33.779 --> 08:35.581
You didn't make a sound.

08:37.316 --> 08:39.452
And I stood there,

08:39.452 --> 08:41.854
and I looked at you,

08:41.854 --> 08:44.991
and you looked at me,

08:44.991 --> 08:46.959
and I had no idea

08:46.959 --> 08:49.128
what you were thinking

08:49.128 --> 08:50.696
and what you felt.

08:52.465 --> 08:54.467
And in that moment,

08:54.467 --> 08:56.469
I had never been so scared

08:56.469 --> 08:59.005
in my entire life.

08:59.005 --> 09:03.309
I thought I knew what fear was
before I had you, but I didn't.

09:03.309 --> 09:05.378
I had no clue.

09:07.747 --> 09:09.181
And no matter what,
everything felt wrong

09:09.181 --> 09:12.151
because I did it.

09:12.151 --> 09:15.154
And no matter what I did,
you were always so far away.

09:18.691 --> 09:21.894
I thought,
"If I just loved you more,

09:21.894 --> 09:23.763
I could get closer."

09:26.699 --> 09:29.268
I loved you so much

09:29.268 --> 09:31.103
that I forgot to breathe.

09:32.738 --> 09:36.509
And then, I ran out of air.

09:39.078 --> 09:41.247
♪

10:00.132 --> 10:02.868
♪

10:17.216 --> 10:18.651
- Hey, you have a light?

10:18.651 --> 10:20.386
- Sorry.

10:24.957 --> 10:27.093
- (man 1): Do you have a light?
- (man 2): Yeah. One second.

10:27.093 --> 10:28.728
- (man 1): Thanks, man.

10:32.898 --> 10:34.533
- Do you have
another one of those?

10:36.502 --> 10:38.804
- Miss Doesn't Have a Light
wants a smoke, I see.

10:53.185 --> 10:55.588
OK if I sit for a sec?
- You just did.

11:08.267 --> 11:11.737
- You look kind of
upset yourself.
- Yeah.

11:13.539 --> 11:15.474
- You don't want
to talk about it?

11:15.474 --> 11:17.410
- Not really but thanks.

11:33.125 --> 11:35.227
(scoffing)

11:35.227 --> 11:36.896
I don't know where to go.

11:40.833 --> 11:42.601
I've just been
sitting here all day.

11:45.037 --> 11:47.707
- Aren't you cold?

11:47.707 --> 11:51.444
- I'm freezing.
♪

12:18.204 --> 12:20.439
(indistinct chatter)

12:36.355 --> 12:38.524
(guitar music playing
on speakers)

12:51.137 --> 12:53.873
(romantic music playing)

13:07.887 --> 13:10.790
(indistinct song playing)
- Kind of a long day, Jordan.

13:12.158 --> 13:13.692
- What happened?

13:16.629 --> 13:18.497
- Um, I...

13:20.065 --> 13:21.967
I'm sorry. I--
- Hey, you... you want

13:21.967 --> 13:23.669
put your head
on my shoulder.

13:29.742 --> 13:33.112
Oh.

13:33.112 --> 13:36.415
You seem like a good person.

13:36.415 --> 13:38.484
- How do you know?

13:40.119 --> 13:42.121
- Your... your face,

13:42.121 --> 13:45.257
your eyes. I can tell.

13:46.659 --> 13:49.929
(indistinct song playing)

13:57.469 --> 14:00.272
- I have a baby...

14:00.272 --> 14:02.875
which is not a baby anymore.

14:02.875 --> 14:05.044
- You're a mom?

14:05.044 --> 14:07.213
That's surreal.

14:07.213 --> 14:09.114
- It is, but, uh...

14:09.114 --> 14:12.518
- I don't know if I'll see her,
and I don't...

14:15.454 --> 14:17.590
- Well, what was
your mom like with you?

14:20.659 --> 14:23.395
- Why would you
ask me that?

14:23.395 --> 14:25.831
- I was just trying
to be helpful.

14:25.831 --> 14:29.001
- No, I haven't seen her
in a long time.

14:29.001 --> 14:31.537
- Well...

14:31.537 --> 14:33.505
I'm still sure
you're the best mom.

14:33.505 --> 14:35.207
I can tell. Remember?

14:35.207 --> 14:37.910
(romantic music playing)

14:40.179 --> 14:41.714
What?

14:44.049 --> 14:46.619
(indistinct romantic song
playing)

15:10.609 --> 15:12.811
These any good?
- Ugh, what do you want?

15:15.414 --> 15:17.449
- Um, sorry.

15:17.449 --> 15:19.351
Can I have
your phone, please?

15:27.459 --> 15:29.328
(man chuckling)
Cool phone.

15:42.241 --> 15:45.144
(door opening and closing)

15:58.090 --> 15:59.558
- Hey, Dad.

16:04.330 --> 16:06.298
- You look rested.

16:09.101 --> 16:11.103
- I'm exhausted.

16:11.103 --> 16:12.571
- Oh, I, uh...

16:16.075 --> 16:18.077
Who... Well, did you see them?

16:21.847 --> 16:23.248
- Sort of.

16:24.750 --> 16:27.119
Dad, when's the last time
that you spoke to Dan?

16:27.119 --> 16:29.288
- Uh...

16:29.288 --> 16:32.324
not too long ago. Uh...

16:32.324 --> 16:34.727
I don't know,
but they seemed OK.

16:36.528 --> 16:39.865
Hey, but you are
here now. Right?

16:39.865 --> 16:42.434
- Yep.

16:42.434 --> 16:45.037
- Hey, you think
you'll be OK on the sofa.

16:45.037 --> 16:46.772
Yeah, you're sure?

16:46.772 --> 16:49.675
Um... is there anything else?

16:52.211 --> 16:54.580
- I'm OK now, really.

16:57.950 --> 17:01.887
- OK, well, I'm just so glad
that... that you're here.

17:01.887 --> 17:03.622
OK, I'll see you
in the morning, sweetheart.

17:18.370 --> 17:20.606
- Hi, Bern.
- Hi.

17:22.808 --> 17:25.911
- I don't bite,
I swear.

17:25.911 --> 17:27.846
- Hi, Dara.

17:27.846 --> 17:29.882
- Hey, Audrey.
- Was the couch alright?

17:31.817 --> 17:35.687
- Hi, sweetheart.
Hey, do you need anything?

17:35.687 --> 17:37.523
- I'm fine, Dad.

17:37.523 --> 17:39.124
- (softly): OK, here.

17:41.093 --> 17:44.830
- OK, we're gonna be late.
Bye, Dara.

17:47.166 --> 17:49.201
- Dad, I'm fine. Really wasn't--
- OK, we gotta run, sweetheart,

17:49.201 --> 17:51.170
but I will see you later,
and then we can catch up, OK?

17:54.239 --> 17:55.941
(door closing)

18:18.030 --> 18:19.965
(door creaking)

18:37.983 --> 18:40.185
(birds singing)

18:51.930 --> 18:53.499
(knocking on door)

18:55.501 --> 18:56.635
(door opening)

19:03.275 --> 19:04.743
- Dara...

19:08.313 --> 19:09.982
Hey.

19:11.750 --> 19:13.819
I'm Thérèse.

19:13.819 --> 19:15.754
- I wanna go up.

19:15.754 --> 19:17.656
- Hi, sweetie.

19:19.491 --> 19:22.294
Hey, can we say hi?

19:22.294 --> 19:23.495
- Hi.

19:23.495 --> 19:25.531
- Hi, Izzy.

19:29.301 --> 19:32.204
Oh, um... Here, I...

19:32.204 --> 19:34.873
I brought this for you.

19:36.642 --> 19:39.878
- I have that.
- Isabel...

19:39.878 --> 19:42.014
- I wanna go down.
- OK.

19:53.392 --> 19:55.294
I don't know what to say.
- How many months?

19:57.029 --> 19:58.597
- Seven.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.470
- Congratulations.

20:05.470 --> 20:07.206
(sighing)

20:09.308 --> 20:11.843
You didn't mention her.

20:11.843 --> 20:14.746
- What?
- Why are you here?

20:14.746 --> 20:17.015
- Oh, I'm... sorry.

20:17.015 --> 20:18.984
I guess that I should
have called first.

20:18.984 --> 20:20.519
- Dan, what's
she talking about?

20:20.519 --> 20:22.921
- Let me deal
with this, OK?

20:22.921 --> 20:24.756
Look, I said
I had to think.

20:26.525 --> 20:28.527
- Does that mean
that I can't see her?

20:28.527 --> 20:31.396
- You made that choice for
everyone two years
ago, remember?

20:40.205 --> 20:43.442
- (Thérèse): Why don't you come
over again another time...

20:43.442 --> 20:45.577
spend some time with her.

20:47.412 --> 20:49.915
- Is that OK with you?

20:49.915 --> 20:51.683
- (Dan): Fine.

20:52.618 --> 20:54.486
- OK, I will, um...

20:57.422 --> 21:00.792
...I will see you soon then.

21:00.792 --> 21:02.761
(indistinct chatter)

21:12.871 --> 21:14.773
(sighing)

21:14.773 --> 21:15.974
- Mm-hmm.

21:20.245 --> 21:21.680
You didn't call.

21:25.150 --> 21:27.286
- There wasn't much to say.

21:32.224 --> 21:33.892
- You look tired.

21:36.662 --> 21:38.497
- Is there
any sub work?

21:42.134 --> 21:44.603
Look, I'm OK now. See?
(Dara chuckling)

21:44.603 --> 21:46.071
- Mm-hmm.

21:47.839 --> 21:49.508
- Can you set a meeting
with Brian?

21:51.343 --> 21:54.279
- He's gone. Retired.

21:54.279 --> 21:56.748
We have Ms. Shaw now.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.555
I'll be in touch, OK?
- OK.

22:16.201 --> 22:19.137
Trying to get rid of me already?
- (Audrey): No, I'm just, uh...

22:19.137 --> 22:21.807
tidying up a bit.
- I can do that.

22:21.807 --> 22:24.276
- No, no, I got it. It's OK.
- No, really.

22:31.850 --> 22:33.618
(clearing her throat)

22:33.618 --> 22:36.788
- So, uh...

22:36.788 --> 22:39.991
do you remember the... realtor

22:39.991 --> 22:41.560
friend of mine
that we were talking about?

22:43.628 --> 22:46.732
Well, I just ran into her
the other day,

22:46.732 --> 22:49.000
and she was telling me
that she has

22:49.000 --> 22:51.103
a lot
of these cute little apartments.

22:53.338 --> 22:55.741
And so I mentioned
your situation.

22:55.741 --> 22:57.376
- You what?

22:59.144 --> 23:01.146
- What?

23:01.146 --> 23:03.215
- I just got back.

23:03.215 --> 23:06.051
- No, no. I...
I didn't mean...

23:06.051 --> 23:08.387
- What did you mean?

23:13.825 --> 23:15.494
- I was just trying to help.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.233
I'm on your side.

23:24.002 --> 23:25.771
- I can take care of myself.

23:31.576 --> 23:33.845
- I could have helped.

23:33.845 --> 23:36.047
That's what couples do,
that's what they do:

23:36.047 --> 23:38.016
they figure things out together.
That's the whole point.

23:40.585 --> 23:42.721
Why didn't you talk to me?
- I tried.

23:42.721 --> 23:45.290
A hundred thousand times, OK?
You told me that...

23:45.290 --> 23:47.626
that I wasn't making sense
and that I was just out of it.

23:49.795 --> 23:52.898
- Why couldn't we
come see you?

23:52.898 --> 23:54.633
- She couldn't see me like that.

23:58.970 --> 24:00.939
- Did you know that she asked
for you every day?

24:04.276 --> 24:06.411
Did you know that?

24:06.411 --> 24:08.413
For months and months,
she looked at me

24:08.413 --> 24:10.315
like I was the wrong person.

24:15.053 --> 24:16.822
- I'm sorry, Dan.

24:18.957 --> 24:22.227
That's the only way
that I could do it.

24:22.227 --> 24:24.296
OK? Myself.

24:29.434 --> 24:31.470
- You look better.

24:34.639 --> 24:35.841
- Thanks.

24:38.944 --> 24:41.012
Look, do you think
that I could spend

24:41.012 --> 24:42.848
a few minutes with her?

24:42.848 --> 24:44.516
- What, you mean alone?

24:48.086 --> 24:49.921
- Why do you
say it like that?

24:56.695 --> 24:59.631
- No, I can't.

24:59.631 --> 25:02.767
And I'm sorry.

25:02.767 --> 25:05.704
(door opening)

25:05.704 --> 25:08.440
(door closing)
- What did you tell her?

25:08.440 --> 25:11.109
- How could I
tell her?

25:11.109 --> 25:13.845
How do you explain this
to a 2-year-old?

25:13.845 --> 25:17.282
(footsteps)

25:22.120 --> 25:24.222
- (Isabel): What's your name?

25:26.224 --> 25:28.727
- It's Dara.

25:30.729 --> 25:33.798
- She's gonna be 4 soon, right?
- (Isabel): My birthday!

25:33.798 --> 25:37.469
- (Dan): Yeah.
- 4? Wow!

25:37.469 --> 25:39.871
- Do you want to come
to my party?

25:39.871 --> 25:41.873
Thérèse is baking a cake.

25:43.975 --> 25:46.778
- Oh, I would love
to come to your party.

25:48.246 --> 25:50.382
- Dad, can we go to the store?

25:50.382 --> 25:53.184
- I'm sorry, honey.
We don't have time right now.

25:53.184 --> 25:55.554
- But, Dad!
- Izz, really, we can't.

25:55.554 --> 25:57.522
- Dad!
- Hey, what did I just say?

25:57.522 --> 25:59.691
- Hey. Hey, Isabel,
can you do something for me?

25:59.691 --> 26:01.593
- What?

26:01.593 --> 26:04.262
- Can you close your eyes
for one second?

26:04.262 --> 26:06.598
Great. Thank you.

26:06.598 --> 26:10.669
If we were in the store
right now, what would you get?

26:10.669 --> 26:14.839
- Chocolate milk.
- Amazing!

26:14.839 --> 26:17.409
I love chocolate milk, too.
Haha!

26:17.409 --> 26:19.945
So, imagine

26:19.945 --> 26:22.581
you're with your dad,
and you're at the store.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.050
Are you in the store?

26:25.050 --> 26:27.085
Hey, I want you to walk
to the fridge,

26:27.085 --> 26:29.754
and I want you to take out
the chocolate milk.

26:29.754 --> 26:31.923
Are you holding it?

26:31.923 --> 26:34.526
Let me see.

26:34.526 --> 26:36.227
OK, now I want you
to open it

26:36.227 --> 26:39.230
and take a big sip.

26:39.230 --> 26:42.467
Now, keep your eyes closed.
You're in the store, remember?

26:42.467 --> 26:44.436
Now, open it

26:44.436 --> 26:46.705
and take a big sip.

26:51.810 --> 26:54.079
How does it taste?

26:54.079 --> 26:56.047
- So good.

26:56.047 --> 26:58.049
(chuckling)
(door closing)

26:58.049 --> 27:00.719
(second door closing)

27:04.089 --> 27:07.926
- I'm so glad you made it.
- Oh, I was just going.

27:07.926 --> 27:10.261
- Are you coming back?

27:10.261 --> 27:13.298
- Of course, sweetheart.

27:13.298 --> 27:15.500
- Well, let me

27:15.500 --> 27:17.636
walk you out then.

27:28.313 --> 27:30.548
I understand
where this puts you.

27:35.286 --> 27:38.556
- You do?
- Yeah, of course.

27:39.824 --> 27:41.860
And I want you
to feel welcome here.

27:41.860 --> 27:45.363
OK? I want to help.

27:45.363 --> 27:47.999
It's so important that
Isabel knows who her mother is.

27:52.604 --> 27:54.773
But I'm here too.

27:57.809 --> 27:59.778
- I can see that.

28:01.312 --> 28:03.114
- He was crushed, you know?

28:06.618 --> 28:08.186
- I know.

28:10.221 --> 28:11.589
- Completely.

28:25.737 --> 28:27.639
(train horn blowing)

28:36.047 --> 28:38.049
- (young manHello?
- (DaraHey. Hi.

28:38.049 --> 28:39.684
Do you, uh...
do you remember me

28:39.684 --> 28:41.986
from the party?
- Jordan: [Yeah, of course.]

28:41.986 --> 28:44.055
[How's it going?]

28:44.055 --> 28:46.391
(scoffing)

28:46.391 --> 28:50.662
- Um... Can we... uh...

28:50.662 --> 28:53.231
Do you want to do
something later?

28:53.231 --> 28:56.101
- (Jordan): Yeah, for sure.
Come over. I'll cook.

28:56.101 --> 28:58.970
- Really?
- Jordan: [Yeah.]

29:02.741 --> 29:05.310
(indistinct song playing
in the background)

29:10.215 --> 29:13.451
And I fight with my dad
all the time.

29:13.451 --> 29:15.253
It's why I decided
to come to school here:

29:15.253 --> 29:17.355
to get away.

29:17.355 --> 29:20.091
- How come?

29:20.091 --> 29:23.261
- 'Cause he doesn't listen.

29:23.261 --> 29:25.630
- Well, how do you
talk to him?

29:29.267 --> 29:31.402
Maybe try talking to him

29:31.402 --> 29:34.572
in a way that you think
that he can hear.

29:34.572 --> 29:37.776
- Why do I have to be
the one to change?

29:37.776 --> 29:39.911
- You don't have
to change anything,

29:39.911 --> 29:42.213
but you want him
to hear you, right?

29:45.049 --> 29:46.518
- Yeah.

29:48.386 --> 29:50.555
So, where's your mom?

29:52.290 --> 29:53.925
- What?

29:53.925 --> 29:56.227
- You said you hadn't
seen her in a long time.

29:58.229 --> 29:59.964
- Uh... She's...

30:01.833 --> 30:04.636
...gone. She left
when I was 4.

30:07.572 --> 30:09.374
- What do you mean,
"She's gone"?

30:12.744 --> 30:15.847
- I don't know.
She just...

30:15.847 --> 30:17.382
left and...

30:19.284 --> 30:21.152
That's it.

30:27.859 --> 30:29.861
- Your daughter's lucky.

30:29.861 --> 30:31.996
- Mm-hmm.

30:31.996 --> 30:34.999
Why is that?

30:34.999 --> 30:36.601
- She has you.

30:39.804 --> 30:41.739
- Lucky? Yeah...

30:47.145 --> 30:48.947
- Show her something.

30:51.316 --> 30:53.484
- Like what?

30:53.484 --> 30:55.887
- She's a kid,
show her anything you want.

30:59.858 --> 31:02.560
- Why are you being
so sweet to me?

31:04.495 --> 31:07.732
- It's just spaghetti.

31:07.732 --> 31:10.401
- Spaghetti is fine by the way--
- Would it be OK if I...

31:13.071 --> 31:14.739
...kissed you?

31:25.049 --> 31:27.919
Oh, I'm sorry.
That was too much.

31:27.919 --> 31:29.988
I thought you looked at me
in a type of way...

31:40.565 --> 31:42.901
- You don't know me at all.

32:32.617 --> 32:35.887
- What is it?
What's wrong?

32:35.887 --> 32:37.822
- Did you know
that Dan is with someone?

32:41.659 --> 32:43.728
Wait. Did you?

32:43.728 --> 32:45.596
- Shh, shh! I-I...

32:45.596 --> 32:48.933
I saw her,
but I-I-I was never sure.

32:48.933 --> 32:51.302
I didn't know. I didn't know
if they were together.

32:54.572 --> 32:56.207
- She's pregnant.

32:58.076 --> 32:59.978
- I'm sorry.

32:59.978 --> 33:02.947
I... I didn't
know that, sweetheart.

33:02.947 --> 33:05.016
I would have told you
if I knew that.

33:07.118 --> 33:08.720
- Dad...

33:13.524 --> 33:15.326
...things aren't...

33:17.328 --> 33:20.531
- Honey, it's all just gonna
take a little bit of time.

33:20.531 --> 33:23.101
OK? That thing,
it-it-it's gonna work out.

33:23.101 --> 33:24.569
You know, I'm telling you.

33:28.172 --> 33:29.574
- I don't know.

33:33.177 --> 33:36.047
- Well, then we'll...
then we should talk about this.

33:36.047 --> 33:38.182
- Dad, we are.

33:38.182 --> 33:40.651
I'm talking about this.
I'm talking about it right now!

33:40.651 --> 33:42.286
- Shhh... No, we're standing
in the hallway

33:42.286 --> 33:44.389
at 1 in the morning.

33:44.389 --> 33:46.657
Tomorrow, OK?

33:46.657 --> 33:48.693
- Why do you
always say that?

33:50.862 --> 33:53.131
- Just go to bed, sweetheart.

33:57.068 --> 33:58.770
- I think about Mom.

34:02.740 --> 34:05.977
I... don't even know
if she's alive, Dad.

34:07.645 --> 34:10.882
But I think about...

34:10.882 --> 34:13.584
who she is now, and...

34:16.354 --> 34:18.256
- Good night.

34:28.566 --> 34:30.835
♪

34:42.780 --> 34:44.749
- (Dara): Is it alright
if I sit down?

34:51.355 --> 34:53.458
Look.

34:53.458 --> 34:57.028
♪

34:57.028 --> 34:59.297
(Dara humming)

35:14.645 --> 35:18.149
See what I did?
Here, watch my fingers. Yes.

35:18.149 --> 35:20.284
♪

35:26.424 --> 35:28.226
Do you want to try?

35:28.226 --> 35:31.462
♪

35:39.504 --> 35:43.407
- We were just about to head out
to the park.

35:43.407 --> 35:45.243
- (Dara): Is it OK
if I tag along?

35:48.179 --> 35:51.749
(kids laughing and chattering)

35:57.688 --> 36:00.324
- What was, uh...

36:00.324 --> 36:02.426
what was that thing?

36:02.426 --> 36:06.197
You did it yesterday
with the... chocolate milk.

36:06.197 --> 36:09.300
- You describe
what you're working toward.

36:09.300 --> 36:11.302
We did it a lot in group,
but I thought

36:11.302 --> 36:13.371
it would calm her down a bit.
- You did.

36:19.310 --> 36:22.180
I can't, uh...

36:22.180 --> 36:25.116
I can't imagine how
any of this is for you.

36:28.119 --> 36:31.155
I don't know,
I just...

36:31.155 --> 36:34.859
I wanted to say that I see you
trying, you know.

36:38.029 --> 36:40.064
- Thanks, Dan.
(cell phone buzzing)

36:40.064 --> 36:42.567
- Yeah.

36:42.567 --> 36:45.636
Oh, shoo, it's Thérèse.
Can you, uh...

36:48.372 --> 36:50.174
...watch her for a minute?

36:50.174 --> 36:52.143
- Of course.

36:52.143 --> 36:53.711
- (Dan): Hello?

36:53.711 --> 36:55.546
Good. Yeah.

36:55.546 --> 36:58.649
(Dara laughing)
Yeah, I know.

36:58.649 --> 37:00.351
(Dan speaking indistinctly)

37:00.351 --> 37:02.420
(kids laughing)

37:02.420 --> 37:04.422
(Dan speaking indistinctly)

37:06.991 --> 37:10.695
Yeah, yeah, she's good.

37:10.695 --> 37:13.664
Yeah.
(kids chatting and laughing)

37:25.576 --> 37:27.545
- Honey, look at me.
Where is she?

37:27.545 --> 37:29.814
Where did she go?
(kids laughing)

37:43.261 --> 37:45.029
Hi!

37:48.966 --> 37:51.769
Hi.
- I'm hiding.

37:51.769 --> 37:53.604
- Can I hide
with you?

38:04.415 --> 38:08.052
It's very orange in here.
- There's an echo.

38:08.052 --> 38:10.821
Hooooo!

38:10.821 --> 38:13.391
Your turn.

38:13.391 --> 38:17.428
- Hoooooo!

38:17.428 --> 38:19.163
Should we try one together?

38:19.163 --> 38:22.733
On three...
One, two,

38:22.733 --> 38:26.137
three!
- (together): Hooooo!

38:26.137 --> 38:28.739
♪

39:00.137 --> 39:03.674
- (Thérèse): You guys coming?
- (Dan): Yeah, just a sec.

39:20.624 --> 39:23.194
- So cute that she invited me
to her party.

39:23.194 --> 39:25.062
- Yeah, you want
to come?

39:25.062 --> 39:28.366
- Uh, I mean, I would
love to, but...

39:28.366 --> 39:30.568
- What?

39:30.568 --> 39:33.971
- Who is gonna be there?
- Just gonna be a bunch of kids.

39:33.971 --> 39:36.707
You won't have
to see anyone.

39:36.707 --> 39:39.243
- OK. Thanks, Dan.

39:39.243 --> 39:40.644
- Hey.

39:46.150 --> 39:47.752
- What?

39:52.156 --> 39:54.125
- Ugh, it's just with...

39:56.026 --> 39:59.296
...Thérèse and with the baby
coming soon...

40:03.334 --> 40:05.069
- You want to divorce me?

40:11.208 --> 40:14.111
Wait. Is that why
you invited me here?

40:16.747 --> 40:18.416
Dan, don't just stand there.
Say something.

40:18.416 --> 40:20.251
- What did you expect?

40:21.919 --> 40:24.555
- Look, I'm better now, OK?
I'm gonna get

40:24.555 --> 40:26.290
my job back, all of it.
- It doesn't matter.

40:26.290 --> 40:28.359
- It does!

40:28.359 --> 40:30.694
How can you say that,
"it doesn't matter"?

40:30.694 --> 40:32.263
Of course it matters!
- Dara, stop yelling.

40:32.263 --> 40:34.498
Just... come here.

40:50.247 --> 40:52.750
- Have you spoken
to a lawyer?

40:52.750 --> 40:54.685
- Yes.

40:56.987 --> 40:59.857
- Was this her idea?
- It wasn't. No.

41:03.961 --> 41:05.863
- What about Isabel?

41:08.132 --> 41:10.401
- It depends.

41:10.401 --> 41:11.735
(scoffing)

41:13.637 --> 41:15.706
- On what?

41:17.908 --> 41:19.710
- It depends
on how you're doing.

41:25.449 --> 41:27.551
Why do you keep
wearing that dress?

41:30.287 --> 41:32.056
What do you think
is gonna happen?

41:39.597 --> 41:42.466
- Look at me, OK?

41:42.466 --> 41:45.002
Look at me.
You can trust me now.

41:53.611 --> 41:55.713
You know I belong here
is right.

41:58.782 --> 42:02.453
OK. You're home for me.
That's it.

42:07.858 --> 42:09.860
Come on, take me back.

42:42.826 --> 42:47.097
- Don't! Don't.
- Don't what, Dan?

42:47.097 --> 42:50.301
(Dan exhaling)

42:57.408 --> 42:59.243
- See you at the party.

43:16.293 --> 43:18.295
- So Nancy says
that you were really...

43:18.295 --> 43:20.531
terrific with the kids.

43:20.531 --> 43:23.233
- It's such a wonderful age -
5, 6 -

43:23.233 --> 43:25.903
you know, you can really
see them coming into themselves

43:25.903 --> 43:29.273
and making choices
and becoming little people.

43:29.273 --> 43:33.877
- It's a fun age.
So you were here for...?

43:33.877 --> 43:36.747
- Seven years.
- That's quite a while.

43:36.747 --> 43:38.716
And you were
gone for...?

43:38.716 --> 43:40.718
- Just a little over two.

43:42.753 --> 43:45.756
- And you decided
just to...

43:45.756 --> 43:47.791
take some time off?
- Well, I had a baby girl.

43:49.560 --> 43:51.829
- It must have been nice
to spend some time with her.

43:54.264 --> 43:56.233
- Yeah. Yeah.

43:56.233 --> 43:58.602
It-it... it really was.

43:58.602 --> 43:59.937
- Both my kids
are all grown now,

43:59.937 --> 44:04.241
but I remember
that time so well.

44:04.241 --> 44:07.044
How old is your daughter?
- She's turning 4 soon.

44:09.146 --> 44:12.683
- Those years are just
incredible, aren't they?

44:12.683 --> 44:15.019
Every moment is a gift.

44:15.019 --> 44:17.121
- Mm-hmm.
- Savour them.

44:17.121 --> 44:19.023
(small chuckle)

44:19.023 --> 44:21.025
Has she lost any teeth yet?
- No, she hasn't.

44:21.025 --> 44:22.459
She hasn't lost any of
her teeth, she has all of them,

44:22.459 --> 44:25.295
but it's enough about her.

44:25.295 --> 44:28.666
- Any more on the way?
- What?

44:28.666 --> 44:31.535
- I'm just curious if you were
planning on having
more children.

44:31.535 --> 44:33.437
- Why is that
any of your business?

44:39.710 --> 44:41.712
- Dara. Dara!

44:44.815 --> 44:46.583
- What are you looking for?

44:53.323 --> 44:54.725
Can I have some?

44:57.528 --> 44:59.730
- How old are you?

44:59.730 --> 45:02.232
- 14. Why, when did you
start drinking?

45:04.168 --> 45:05.636
- It was 14.

45:09.039 --> 45:12.076
No, it's not a good idea.
- Dad lets me.

45:12.076 --> 45:15.579
- I doubt that's true.
- He gave me some
at a wedding once.

45:15.579 --> 45:18.549
Honestly.

45:18.549 --> 45:21.652
- Fine. A little.

45:43.741 --> 45:45.476
- I feel weird.

45:47.578 --> 45:48.946
- That means it's working.

45:50.414 --> 45:53.617
- And people like this?

45:53.617 --> 45:55.886
- Where's your mother?

45:55.886 --> 45:58.589
- I don't know.
Why do people like this stuff?

46:00.691 --> 46:03.627
- Because it's different.

46:03.627 --> 46:05.529
- And then,
what do they do?

46:08.198 --> 46:10.234
- Dance,

46:10.234 --> 46:12.903
tell secrets,

46:12.903 --> 46:14.271
cry.

46:20.043 --> 46:23.914
- ♪ What is Ryan thinking ♪

46:23.914 --> 46:28.152
♪ Why is Ashley mad at me ♪

46:28.152 --> 46:30.921
♪ Why are boys such jerks ♪

46:30.921 --> 46:32.856
♪ And girls little bitches ♪

46:34.658 --> 46:36.460
(sighing)

46:38.295 --> 46:40.864
(laughing)

46:47.070 --> 46:48.539
(chuckling)

46:51.575 --> 46:53.577
- Are you OK?

46:59.616 --> 47:01.685
(chuckling)

47:04.321 --> 47:07.858
- What? It's cute, no?
- Where did you get that?

47:07.858 --> 47:09.860
- I found a box of stuff
in the garage.

47:09.860 --> 47:11.762
Tons of cool crap.

47:11.762 --> 47:14.498
Why do you look like that?

47:14.498 --> 47:17.835
- I think it was my mom's,
that's all.

47:17.835 --> 47:20.671
- Oh.

47:26.643 --> 47:29.546
- Why are you
wearing that?

47:29.546 --> 47:32.416
- I was cold. Now I'm not, and
I don't want to be cold again.

47:34.284 --> 47:35.953
- Are you OK?

47:35.953 --> 47:37.888
- I mean, it's bad
if I close my eyes.

47:40.057 --> 47:41.625
- Here.

47:50.901 --> 47:53.470
- Can I ask you a question?

47:53.470 --> 47:55.138
- Sure.

47:58.709 --> 48:01.712
It's fine, Bernie,
you can ask.

48:07.684 --> 48:09.753
- Did you get
electric shocks?

48:13.924 --> 48:15.726
- I didn't need that.

48:18.362 --> 48:21.098
- Oh. What was
the hospital like?

48:25.769 --> 48:29.740
- It was... long...

48:36.513 --> 48:38.248
...scary sometimes.

48:41.718 --> 48:44.021
- How did your mom die?

48:46.590 --> 48:48.926
- Who told you that she died?

49:00.137 --> 49:02.806
(dog barking)

49:19.623 --> 49:21.825
(crow cawing)

49:41.011 --> 49:44.047
- (Bernie): I don't feel good.
- (Audrey): What is it, sweetie?

49:51.755 --> 49:53.557
- I was drinking before
with Dara.

49:55.292 --> 49:59.129
- (Audrey): Drinking? What...
what do you mean, drinking?

49:59.129 --> 50:02.366
- Dara, I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to tell. I'm sorry.

50:04.501 --> 50:06.937
- She's 14.
- Exactly. I just gave her

50:06.937 --> 50:09.106
a bit. It's like at a wedding.

50:09.106 --> 50:10.874
- (Dara's father):
This is not a wedding.

50:12.642 --> 50:15.679
- (Audrey): What did I tell you?
- Hell, what did she tell you?

50:17.647 --> 50:19.683
- (Audrey): Come.
(Dara's father sighing)

50:27.624 --> 50:29.459
(sighing)

50:44.207 --> 50:47.010
- Wha...

50:47.010 --> 50:48.545
- Dad...

50:54.418 --> 50:56.153
Say something.
- What?

50:59.022 --> 51:01.725
She wrote. What?

51:01.725 --> 51:03.760
That was over
five years ago now.

51:07.531 --> 51:09.733
She needed
something signed.

51:11.701 --> 51:13.937
- And that's her address?

51:13.937 --> 51:16.006
- (Dara's father):
Yeah, it was, it was then, yeah.

51:19.609 --> 51:21.812
- She lives an hour from here.

51:23.547 --> 51:25.515
(Dara's father sighing)

51:25.515 --> 51:28.085
Why didn't you tell me?

51:28.085 --> 51:29.986
- Dara, you were pregnant.

51:31.555 --> 51:34.091
You were starting your life.

51:34.091 --> 51:36.359
OK? We hadn't...
we hadn't spoken about her

51:36.359 --> 51:39.563
in so many years and...

51:39.563 --> 51:42.265
and she didn't ask.

51:42.265 --> 51:44.367
- Why do we tell people
that she's dead?

51:48.138 --> 51:50.707
She's not, Dad.

51:50.707 --> 51:52.542
We can't keep
living this way,

51:52.542 --> 51:54.911
just pretending and lying.

51:54.911 --> 51:57.714
- She... she left us.

51:57.714 --> 51:59.649
She left you.

52:04.821 --> 52:07.557
- Why didn't you come see me?

52:07.557 --> 52:09.025
- But I did.
- Once.

52:11.094 --> 52:14.164
You came once.
And I asked you to come back.

52:14.164 --> 52:17.400
And-and-and I needed you there
and I told you that!

52:17.400 --> 52:20.604
- And I tried, I tried.
That whole thing just felt

52:20.604 --> 52:22.572
all... just felt again like...
I don't know.

52:22.572 --> 52:24.774
- Like what, Dad? Like her?

52:24.774 --> 52:26.977
- Uh, no,
that's not what I meant.

52:26.977 --> 52:28.678
- It was.

52:34.317 --> 52:35.986
Dad...

52:38.455 --> 52:40.790
...I don't know what to do.

52:40.790 --> 52:42.926
- Just... try
to be a mother.

52:45.128 --> 52:46.530
- What?

52:48.698 --> 52:51.168
How can you say that?
Like... Like, oh, like,

52:51.168 --> 52:53.770
"try to be a mother." Like,
like... like it's a sentence!

52:53.770 --> 52:55.872
- It's a sentence.
- No, it isn't.

52:55.872 --> 52:59.309
It's a million little decisions
one after the other,

52:59.309 --> 53:01.311
after the other, after the--
- I know. OK, OK,

53:01.311 --> 53:03.780
OK. Just... All you can do

53:03.780 --> 53:06.082
is your best, sweetheart. OK?

53:25.001 --> 53:28.405
- My mom lives
only an hour from here.

53:28.405 --> 53:31.041
- That's great. Hmm...

53:32.876 --> 53:34.544
What does that mean?

53:37.314 --> 53:40.050
- I don't know.

53:40.050 --> 53:41.885
(men inside speaking
indistinctly)

53:44.588 --> 53:46.723
- Hmm... how's your girl?

53:46.723 --> 53:49.659
- She's good.

53:49.659 --> 53:51.861
- You show her something?

53:51.861 --> 53:54.130
- I did.

53:55.498 --> 53:56.900
- See?

53:59.102 --> 54:00.704
- Another party?

54:00.704 --> 54:02.906
(man speaking indistinctly)
- Mm-mm. No,

54:02.906 --> 54:05.575
just a couple buds.
We're supposed to be studying

54:05.575 --> 54:08.178
for a test
tomorrow, but...

54:08.178 --> 54:10.347
But you want to come in
and chill for a sec

54:10.347 --> 54:11.915
or stay over?

54:13.750 --> 54:17.087
(bubbling noise)
(gunshots from TV)

54:19.222 --> 54:21.258
- You know what?
I don't think

54:21.258 --> 54:23.293
that that's a good idea.

54:30.600 --> 54:33.970
But thanks. You're a sweet kid.

54:42.979 --> 54:46.783
(kids chattering and laughing)
(Dara taking a deep breath)

54:58.728 --> 55:01.998
Hi, sweetheart.
- It's my birthday!

55:01.998 --> 55:04.501
- What?! No!

55:04.501 --> 55:06.503
I didn't bring you anything.

55:06.503 --> 55:09.939
- Really?
- I had no idea.

55:09.939 --> 55:14.044
But wait, I guess
that's why I brought you this.

55:15.578 --> 55:18.948
- Uh, it's for me?
What's his name?

55:18.948 --> 55:21.184
- Well, it's a Jack Dempsey,

55:21.184 --> 55:23.687
so I thought we could call it
Jack. That's my dad's name.

55:39.969 --> 55:42.072
I'm gonna go put Jack
in some water.

55:43.707 --> 55:45.942
(laughing)
(upbeat music playing)

55:55.719 --> 55:57.787
(roaring)

55:58.288 --> 56:00.123
(roaring)

56:07.864 --> 56:10.367
- (male singer): ♪ Looking
from the window above ♪

56:10.367 --> 56:12.469
♪ It's like a story of love ♪

56:12.469 --> 56:14.304
- Everyone, come here.

56:14.304 --> 56:16.740
Come here! Come on, you guys!

56:16.740 --> 56:19.676
- ♪ Came back only yesterday ♪

56:19.676 --> 56:22.579
♪ I'm moving farther away ♪

56:22.579 --> 56:25.582
♪ Want you near me ♪

56:25.582 --> 56:30.687
(Dara lip-synching): ♪ All
I needed was to love you gave ♪

56:30.687 --> 56:34.157
♪ All I needed for another day ♪

56:34.157 --> 56:38.495
♪ And all I ever knew ♪

56:38.495 --> 56:40.430
♪ Only you ♪

56:43.933 --> 56:46.603
♪ Sometimes when I think
of her name ♪

56:46.603 --> 56:49.939
♪ When it's only a game ♪

56:49.939 --> 56:53.042
♪ And I need you ♪

56:53.042 --> 56:55.879
♪ Listen to the words
that you say ♪

56:55.879 --> 56:59.015
♪ It's getting harder to stay ♪

56:59.015 --> 57:02.051
♪ When I see you ♪

57:02.051 --> 57:04.287
- Come here.
- ♪ All I needed was ♪

57:04.287 --> 57:06.790
♪ The love you gave ♪

57:06.790 --> 57:10.794
♪ All I needed for another day ♪

57:10.794 --> 57:14.564
♪ And all I ever knew ♪

57:14.564 --> 57:16.933
♪ Only you ♪

57:16.933 --> 57:19.035
- (Isabel): Mommy!

57:22.372 --> 57:25.041
Mommy!
- (Dara): Hi.

57:25.041 --> 57:26.743
It's OK, Iz. It's fine,

57:26.743 --> 57:29.045
it's me. OK, Iz.

57:29.045 --> 57:31.748
Isabel, it's fine, it's me.
- Mommy.

57:31.748 --> 57:34.150
- It's me, Isabel.
♪

57:34.150 --> 57:36.820
- Mommy!

57:36.820 --> 57:39.255
- No, please. Let me do this,
please. I got it.

57:39.255 --> 57:41.057
- ♪ All I needed was
the love you gave ♪

57:41.057 --> 57:43.326
- No! No-no!
- Wait, Dara!
- No!

57:43.326 --> 57:45.195
(silence)

58:06.483 --> 58:10.153
Is she OK?
- She's just shaken up a bit.

58:10.153 --> 58:12.522
She hurt her elbow.
She's fine.

58:12.522 --> 58:14.524
- (Thérèse): This is my fault.

58:14.524 --> 58:16.526
I pushed this
too hard.

58:16.526 --> 58:19.829
- OK, trust me,
this is not about you.

58:19.829 --> 58:22.465
- Dara, think of Isabel.

58:22.465 --> 58:24.767
- OK, Thérèse,

58:24.767 --> 58:27.170
you are sitting in my kitchen

58:27.170 --> 58:30.039
at my table
with my husband right there

58:30.039 --> 58:31.975
and my kid in the next room, OK?
I bought the chair

58:31.975 --> 58:33.977
that you are sitting on.
- (Dan): OK, hey,

58:33.977 --> 58:36.513
don't speak to her like that.
- OK, Dan,

58:36.513 --> 58:38.281
you let our daughter
call this woman Mommy?

58:38.281 --> 58:41.484
What is she even doing here?
- He's not your husband.

58:41.484 --> 58:43.653
He was, but he's not anymore.
- Who are you?

58:43.653 --> 58:46.890
What are you doing in my house?!
- I'm the woman raising
your daughter!

58:46.890 --> 58:48.758
- I am her mother!
- Are you?

58:53.963 --> 58:56.332
- What, that is my mug.

58:56.332 --> 58:58.334
What are you doing
drinking out of

58:58.334 --> 59:00.003
my mug?!
- What are you doing?!

59:00.003 --> 59:02.071
What are you doing?
You're acting crazy.

59:03.973 --> 59:06.009
This is just like before;
you don't make sense, Dara!

59:06.009 --> 59:08.478
- No, I... I do.
- No, you don't!

59:08.478 --> 59:11.080
- I do, I do make sense, OK?

59:11.080 --> 59:14.851
I'm not crazy,
and I wasn't crazy before.

59:14.851 --> 59:17.687
I had her and I got sick,

59:17.687 --> 59:19.989
and this is exactly
why I had to leave:

59:19.989 --> 59:22.926
because you made me feel
like I was crazy.

59:22.926 --> 59:24.727
- How did I make you feel crazy?
- (Thérèse): Let her talk.

59:32.201 --> 59:35.905
- Look, you didn't
understand me then,

59:35.905 --> 59:37.974
and you still don't
understand me now.

59:43.246 --> 59:44.781
OK, so... so tell me,

59:44.781 --> 59:47.350
what do you do? "You get better,

59:47.350 --> 59:49.118
"and the only way
that you know how.

59:49.118 --> 59:52.121
And you do that every day
a little bit."

59:52.121 --> 59:54.424
That's what they said,
"That you can't see it,

59:54.424 --> 59:57.193
but it's there and it adds up."

59:57.193 --> 59:59.262
That's what they told me,
that it adds up.

59:59.262 --> 1:00:02.031
And so you take
what they tell you to take,

1:00:02.031 --> 1:00:04.367
even if it makes you
not you anymore,

1:00:04.367 --> 1:00:07.236
and then you feel
like you're somebody else.

1:00:07.236 --> 1:00:10.206
But you do that, and you do it
and you keep doing it

1:00:10.206 --> 1:00:12.308
until they tell you
that you're OK.

1:00:15.712 --> 1:00:18.648
Look, I went away to get better,

1:00:18.648 --> 1:00:20.950
so that I could come back

1:00:20.950 --> 1:00:23.019
and be in this family
the right way...

1:00:25.555 --> 1:00:27.457
...if I'm still welcome.

1:00:39.669 --> 1:00:41.204
You didn't wait.

1:00:43.339 --> 1:00:45.274
Hey, Dan, I told you
that I was gonna come back.

1:00:45.274 --> 1:00:47.310
I promised you that, OK?

1:00:47.310 --> 1:00:49.812
I'm not her.
I am not my mom!

1:00:52.015 --> 1:00:54.517
But...

1:00:56.185 --> 1:00:58.321
I'm sorry. Look, I'm sorry, OK?

1:00:58.321 --> 1:01:00.256
Look, just...

1:01:00.256 --> 1:01:03.326
just tell me
who you want me to be,

1:01:03.326 --> 1:01:05.495
and then I'll just be her, OK?

1:01:05.495 --> 1:01:07.697
Just... just let me stay

1:01:07.697 --> 1:01:10.299
and I'll be so good, I promise.

1:01:10.299 --> 1:01:13.202
OK? I'll make myself so small
you won't even notice me.

1:01:13.202 --> 1:01:15.471
I'll live in the walls or...

1:01:15.471 --> 1:01:17.473
or you can put me in the closet,

1:01:17.473 --> 1:01:19.676
and I won't make a peep.

1:01:19.676 --> 1:01:22.779
I... I can be Aunt Dara or...

1:01:24.547 --> 1:01:26.949
No. No, never mind,

1:01:26.949 --> 1:01:28.918
I take that back. Don't call me
that, that'd really hurt.

1:01:31.487 --> 1:01:33.690
Here, look, I can...
Here, look, I...

1:01:33.690 --> 1:01:36.392
how I can just fit
on one tile, OK?

1:01:36.392 --> 1:01:38.895
So small. Look, I can just...

1:01:38.895 --> 1:01:40.863
I can just...
I can just... live here.

1:01:40.863 --> 1:01:43.299
I'll just stay right here. OK?

1:01:43.299 --> 1:01:44.767
- (Isabel): Dad...

1:01:46.803 --> 1:01:48.504
- (Dan): OK, Isabel.
- (Dara): No, no, no!

1:01:48.504 --> 1:01:51.841
- Izzy, Izzy. Come here, baby.
Come here. Hey, you're OK.

1:01:51.841 --> 1:01:54.077
Hey, it's OK.
Come here. It's OK.

1:01:54.077 --> 1:01:55.745
- (Dara): Can you...
can you turn on the lights?

1:01:55.745 --> 1:01:57.680
- It's OK, honey.

1:01:57.680 --> 1:01:59.916
- Can someone please turn on
the lights, please?!

1:02:02.218 --> 1:02:04.921
I need to talk to her.
I wanna talk to her alone.
- (Dan): No.

1:02:04.921 --> 1:02:07.156
- Look, I-I-I-I did it
wrong before, OK?

1:02:07.156 --> 1:02:08.991
Isabel, I should have

1:02:08.991 --> 1:02:11.027
told you before that I'm...

1:02:11.027 --> 1:02:13.162
Come on, just please...

1:02:13.162 --> 1:02:15.231
Just... just come here for...

1:02:15.231 --> 1:02:17.400
Just look at me.
- (Thérèse): You're scaring us.

1:02:20.036 --> 1:02:21.904
- But this is my family.

1:02:23.906 --> 1:02:25.908
Just please come here
for one second.

1:02:25.908 --> 1:02:28.778
Please, baby,
just... just for one second.

1:02:28.778 --> 1:02:31.748
Just look at me.
(breathing hard)

1:02:31.748 --> 1:02:33.316
Just please.

1:02:35.184 --> 1:02:36.619
- (Isabel): Go!

1:02:48.131 --> 1:02:49.766
- OK.

1:02:54.137 --> 1:02:56.539
OK, I'm gonna go.

1:02:56.539 --> 1:02:58.274
I'm so sorry.

1:03:02.979 --> 1:03:05.414
OK, OK, OK.
I'm going. I'm going.

1:03:05.414 --> 1:03:08.050
I'm going. I got it.

1:03:11.721 --> 1:03:14.557
(Dara breathing heavy)

1:03:18.795 --> 1:03:20.797
♪

1:03:29.005 --> 1:03:31.007
♪

