(crickets chirping)

1:04:03.673 --> 1:04:05.908
(breathing audibly)

1:04:10.146 --> 1:04:11.714
(gulping)

1:04:54.991 --> 1:04:57.059
(birds singing)

1:05:09.372 --> 1:05:11.974
(birds singing)

1:05:55.217 --> 1:05:57.286
(birds singing)

1:06:35.157 --> 1:06:38.694
(audible breathing)

1:06:54.677 --> 1:06:57.046
(wind blowing)

1:07:14.397 --> 1:07:17.199
(knocking on door)

1:07:19.468 --> 1:07:21.404
- Well, hello there.

1:07:21.404 --> 1:07:23.272
What can I do for you?

1:07:28.077 --> 1:07:30.713
- I...

1:07:30.713 --> 1:07:32.982
have the wrong address. Sorry.

1:07:56.605 --> 1:07:59.208
(car key turning)
(engine revving up)

1:07:59.208 --> 1:08:01.577
(gear stick shifting)

1:08:30.973 --> 1:08:32.908
(gear stick shifting)

1:08:32.908 --> 1:08:34.810
(car key turning)
(engine stopping)

1:08:45.121 --> 1:08:46.889
- (woman): I'll be
with you in a sec!

1:08:59.001 --> 1:09:01.003
Sorry about that.
How can I help you?

1:09:05.007 --> 1:09:07.409
We got lots
of wonderful stuff here.

1:09:07.409 --> 1:09:09.311
We've got some...

1:09:09.311 --> 1:09:11.647
t-shirts and sweatshirts

1:09:11.647 --> 1:09:14.250
and little knickknacks
that make great gifts.

1:09:14.250 --> 1:09:16.185
Who are you shopping
for today?

1:09:19.922 --> 1:09:22.158
OK, well, I'll just be
right over there

1:09:22.158 --> 1:09:24.860
if you need anything.

1:09:45.114 --> 1:09:47.483
- I'm looking for my daughter.

1:09:47.483 --> 1:09:49.485
- How old is she?

1:09:49.485 --> 1:09:51.387
- She's 4.

1:09:51.387 --> 1:09:55.157
- Well.. what about...

1:09:55.157 --> 1:09:58.294
one of these...

1:09:58.294 --> 1:10:00.229
Aww!

1:10:00.229 --> 1:10:02.464
This is cute, don't you think?
(chuckling)

1:10:04.166 --> 1:10:06.502
Or... we also have

1:10:06.502 --> 1:10:09.138
some children's books
you might like here.

1:10:09.138 --> 1:10:11.674
Ummm...

1:10:11.674 --> 1:10:13.542
- Do you have any for the piano?

1:10:15.377 --> 1:10:17.780
- You know what? Yeah.

1:10:27.923 --> 1:10:32.661
You're in luck. We just had
a music exhibit here last month.

1:10:32.661 --> 1:10:34.763
- Perfect.

1:10:34.763 --> 1:10:36.532
- I used
to play, actually,

1:10:36.532 --> 1:10:39.501
a million years ago.

1:10:39.501 --> 1:10:41.170
- Oh yeah?

1:10:46.375 --> 1:10:48.277
- Well, I'll just ring it up.

1:10:57.519 --> 1:10:59.755
(cash register beeping)

1:11:01.257 --> 1:11:03.192
That's $10 even.

1:11:04.760 --> 1:11:07.663
(cash register
opening and closing)

1:11:09.798 --> 1:11:11.533
- Do you like working here?

1:11:11.533 --> 1:11:13.269
- Yeah, it's OK.

1:11:13.269 --> 1:11:16.105
It's quiet.

1:11:16.105 --> 1:11:18.540
- You've been here long?
- Couple of years, I guess.

1:11:18.540 --> 1:11:20.709
We live just down the road.

1:11:20.709 --> 1:11:24.947
- We?
- My husband and I. Bruce.

1:11:24.947 --> 1:11:27.983
- Do you like living here?
- Oh, I love it here.

1:11:27.983 --> 1:11:30.286
It's so peaceful.

1:11:30.286 --> 1:11:32.121
Are you not from around here?

1:11:33.822 --> 1:11:35.424
- No.

1:11:35.424 --> 1:11:37.760
- Just visiting?

1:11:37.760 --> 1:11:39.628
- I am.

1:11:44.166 --> 1:11:47.202
- Is there anything else
I can for you, sweetheart?

1:11:57.346 --> 1:11:58.247
- No.

1:12:00.115 --> 1:12:02.518
There's nothing else
that you can do for me.

1:12:05.487 --> 1:12:08.924
I left my daughter.

1:12:08.924 --> 1:12:11.527
I couldn't handle it,
being a mother.

1:12:13.762 --> 1:12:15.764
But I went to get help,

1:12:15.764 --> 1:12:18.000
and I got better.

1:12:19.501 --> 1:12:21.437
And I came back.

1:12:26.775 --> 1:12:28.444
Thanks for your time.

1:12:29.845 --> 1:12:32.381
(footsteps)

1:12:32.381 --> 1:12:35.050
(door opening)

1:12:35.050 --> 1:12:36.585
(door closing)

1:13:16.525 --> 1:13:18.227
(engine revving up)

1:13:33.208 --> 1:13:35.010
♪

1:13:45.521 --> 1:13:48.457
I just saw her, Catherine.

1:13:48.457 --> 1:13:50.759
- (Jack): What?

1:13:50.759 --> 1:13:53.262
What, just now? Are you OK?

1:13:53.262 --> 1:13:55.964
- (Dara): Honestly, Dad,

1:13:55.964 --> 1:13:58.233
I'm fine.

1:13:58.233 --> 1:13:59.868
- (Jack): I don't understand.
You spoke to her?

1:13:59.868 --> 1:14:02.404
- (Dara): I did.

1:14:02.404 --> 1:14:05.841
It was... weird at first, but...

1:14:08.610 --> 1:14:11.647
I don't know, she's just

1:14:11.647 --> 1:14:13.715
some woman.

1:14:15.951 --> 1:14:18.887
- (Jack):
Be patient with yourself.

1:14:18.887 --> 1:14:21.723
You need to look ahead now.

1:14:21.723 --> 1:14:24.026
Not behind you.

1:14:27.429 --> 1:14:29.665
Sweetheart, are you still there?

1:14:29.665 --> 1:14:31.800
- (DaraYeah, Dad.

1:14:31.800 --> 1:14:33.535
I am.

1:14:41.410 --> 1:14:43.245
You didn't hang up.

1:14:43.245 --> 1:14:45.080
- Dan: [No, I didn't.]

1:14:47.249 --> 1:14:49.518
- Can I talk to her
for a second, please?

1:14:57.860 --> 1:14:59.761
Do you know
if it's a boy or a girl?

1:15:01.497 --> 1:15:03.565
- [It's a girl.]

1:15:05.501 --> 1:15:07.269
- Two girls.

1:15:11.039 --> 1:15:13.008
Look, we'll get
the divorce stuff started

1:15:13.008 --> 1:15:14.910
right away, OK?
Whatever you want.

1:15:16.612 --> 1:15:19.681
- Dan: [I never...]

1:15:19.681 --> 1:15:23.218
[I never thought
that you were crazy.]

1:15:23.218 --> 1:15:25.454
[I was just... I don't know,]

1:15:25.454 --> 1:15:27.523
[sometimes, you were
a completely different person.]

1:15:29.491 --> 1:15:31.193
- That was me, Dan.

1:15:33.495 --> 1:15:35.731
- I should have listened to you.

1:15:35.731 --> 1:15:39.134
- Well,

1:15:39.134 --> 1:15:41.770
she's gonna need you
just like I did.

1:15:43.472 --> 1:15:45.040
- I did wait.

1:15:45.040 --> 1:15:48.243
I did. How could I know?

1:16:01.156 --> 1:16:02.891
- I don't know where to go.

1:16:06.361 --> 1:16:09.064
Dan...

1:16:09.064 --> 1:16:10.699
- Yeah?

1:16:10.699 --> 1:16:13.468
- Can I talk to her, please?

1:16:18.707 --> 1:16:20.876
- I'm gonna stay on the line.

1:16:20.876 --> 1:16:22.945
- Yeah. Oh yeah, of course.

1:16:26.348 --> 1:16:29.351
- Dan: [Isabel?]

1:16:29.351 --> 1:16:31.820
[Hey, Isabel.
Someone wants to talk to you.]

1:16:35.691 --> 1:16:38.293
- Isabel: [Hello?]

1:16:38.293 --> 1:16:40.696
- Hi, sweetheart.

1:16:42.431 --> 1:16:44.132
How are you?

1:16:46.101 --> 1:16:48.704
- [OK.]

1:16:48.704 --> 1:16:51.073
- How's your arm?

1:16:51.073 --> 1:16:52.808
- [It's OK.]

1:16:55.978 --> 1:16:57.846
- You're so strong.

1:17:05.053 --> 1:17:08.390
I'm sorry
that I scared you before.

1:17:08.390 --> 1:17:11.226
I just, uh... I just get

1:17:11.226 --> 1:17:13.729
too excited sometimes,

1:17:13.729 --> 1:17:16.331
but I'm gonna work on that.

1:17:16.331 --> 1:17:19.267
And...

1:17:19.267 --> 1:17:23.538
I wanna really try to be
a good mom for you.

1:17:26.608 --> 1:17:28.410
(footsteps over phone)

1:17:31.313 --> 1:17:33.448
- Dan: [We should go.]

1:17:33.448 --> 1:17:35.684
- Of course. OK.

1:17:35.684 --> 1:17:38.186
Alright. Goodbye, sweetheart.

1:17:38.186 --> 1:17:39.888
- Isabel: [Bye, Dara.]

1:17:43.859 --> 1:17:46.828
- Dan: [She's gone.]

1:17:46.828 --> 1:17:48.697
- Yeah.

1:17:52.934 --> 1:17:55.003
- [You're gonna be OK there?]

1:17:56.471 --> 1:17:59.207
- Yeah. I will.

1:18:13.021 --> 1:18:14.956
- (Dan): I'm gonna talk
to you soon, OK?

1:18:17.392 --> 1:18:20.862
- (DaraThank you.
- (Dan): For what?

1:18:20.862 --> 1:18:23.598
- (Dara):    For being there
for her when I couldn't.

1:18:25.734 --> 1:18:27.369
- (Dan): She's our girl.

1:18:29.371 --> 1:18:31.073
- (Dara): Yeah, she is.

1:19:14.549 --> 1:19:16.585
(turning off tap water)

1:19:16.585 --> 1:19:19.554
Isabel...
♪

1:19:19.554 --> 1:19:21.523
...when you were born,
my first thought

1:19:21.523 --> 1:19:23.358
was, "What did I just do?"

1:19:25.026 --> 1:19:26.995
Now, you had me as a mother.

1:19:28.597 --> 1:19:30.599
When we were ready
to leave the hospital,

1:19:30.599 --> 1:19:33.101
a nurse just handed you to me,
and I thought,

1:19:33.101 --> 1:19:35.036
"How is that possible?"

1:19:36.738 --> 1:19:39.608
My best wasn't good enough.

1:19:39.608 --> 1:19:41.476
I know that.
♪

1:19:41.476 --> 1:19:44.780
And I don't know
if I'll ever get it right...

1:19:46.715 --> 1:19:49.618
...but there's time,

1:19:49.618 --> 1:19:52.888
and I'll try again,

1:19:52.888 --> 1:19:57.592
and again,

1:19:57.592 --> 1:19:59.327
and again.

